 {"id":"frankenredis-6axy","title":"Add concurrent WATCH/MULTI/EXEC transaction isolation integration test","description":"# Transaction Isolation Under Concurrency\n\n## What\nTest that WATCH + MULTI/EXEC provides proper optimistic locking when multiple clients race on the same key. This is a core Redis guarantee.\n\n## Why\nThe existing tcp_e2e tests only test single-client transactions. Real deployments depend on WATCH to detect conflicts. If this is broken, data corruption occurs silently.\n\n## Implementation\n1. Add to crates/fr-server/tests/concurrent_e2e.rs\n2. Test scenario:\n   - Client A: WATCH key, GET key → \"0\"\n   - Client B: SET key \"1\" (modifies the watched key)  \n   - Client A: MULTI, SET key \"2\", EXEC\n   - Client A EXEC should return nil (transaction aborted due to WATCH)\n   - GET key should be \"1\" (Client B value, not Client A)\n3. Repeat 100 times with random timing to stress-test\n\n## Logging\n- Log each client operation with timestamp and thread ID\n- Log EXEC result (success vs abort) for each iteration\n- Summary: \"N/100 transactions correctly aborted\"\n\n## Files\n- crates/fr-server/tests/concurrent_e2e.rs","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T04:15:36.432096682Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T19:10:15.890945475Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T19:10:15.890680533Z","close_reason":"Added 2 WATCH/MULTI/EXEC E2E tests: tcp_watch_exec_aborts_on_concurrent_modification (proves WATCH detects cross-client modification and aborts EXEC with null array) and tcp_watch_exec_succeeds_without_concurrent_modification (proves clean EXEC returns results). Both pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
