 {"id":"frankenredis-cf6d","title":"Fix failing replica_stream_reconnect_uses_partial_psync_after_disconnect test","description":"The test replica_stream_reconnect_uses_partial_psync_after_disconnect is failing with:\n- Warning: 'primary closed replication stream during sync'\n- Assertion: gamma key returns nil instead of '3'\n\nThe test verifies that after a primary disconnect and reconnect, the replica receives data via CONTINUE sync. The failure suggests the CONTINUE sync isn't completing properly.\n\nPotential causes:\n1. EOF detection before buffer is fully processed\n2. Timing issues in the mock primary server\n3. Possible regression from commit 23a9eb6 (fail CONTINUE sync on primary disconnect)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-13T17:42:15.419866253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-13T17:47:44.532268388Z","closed_at":"2026-04-13T17:47:44.532079690Z","close_reason":"Fixed: Modified run_replica_sync to process buffered data before erroring on disconnect. Unit test replica_stream_reconnect_uses_partial_psync_after_disconnect now passes (48/48 unit tests pass).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["replication","server","test"]}
